<LocalizedProperties><Language>en</Language><Title>Security Update for Microsoft Windows 2000 (KB826232)</Title><Description>A security issue has been identified that could allow an attacker to read files or run programs on a computer, running Microsoft® Windows® 2000, that has been used to view an attacker's Web site or has read a specially crafted HTML e-mail. You can help protect your computer by installing this update from Microsoft. After you install this item, you may have to restart your computer.</Description><MoreInfoUrl>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=19232</MoreInfoUrl><SupportUrl>http://support.microsoft.com</SupportUrl></LocalizedProperties>